{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":560,"text":"Half of the human workforce\nis expected to be replaced"},{"time":4160,"text":"by software and robots\nin the next 20 years."},{"time":7480,"text":"And many corporate leaders welcome\nthat as a chance to increase profits."},{"time":12600,"text":"Machines are more efficient;"},{"time":14840,"text":"humans are complicated\nand difficult to manage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":19720,"text":"Well, I want our organizations\nto remain human."},{"time":25200,"text":"In fact, I want them to become beautiful."},{"time":29120,"text":"Because as machines take our jobs\nand do them more efficiently,"},{"time":32759,"text":"soon the only work left for us humans\nwill be the kind of work"},{"time":37000,"text":"that must be done beautifully\nrather than efficiently."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41760,"text":"To maintain our humanity\nin the this second Machine Age,"},{"time":44960,"text":"we may have no other choice\nthan to create beauty."},{"time":50240,"text":"Beauty is an elusive concept."},{"time":52480,"text":"For the writer Stendhal\nit was the promise of happiness."},{"time":56520,"text":"For me it's a goal by Lionel Messi."}]},{"cues":[{"time":58880,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":60320,"text":"So bear with me"},{"time":61920,"text":"as I am proposing four admittedly\nvery subjective principles"},{"time":66320,"text":"that you can use to build\na beautiful organization."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69960,"text":"First: do the unnecessary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72520,"text":"[Do the Unnecessary]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":73760,"text":"A few months ago, Hamdi Ulukaya,"},{"time":75320,"text":"the CEO and founder\nof the yogurt company Chobani,"},{"time":78480,"text":"made headlines when he decided to grant\nstock to all of his 2,000 employees."},{"time":83600,"text":"Some called it a PR stunt,"},{"time":85560,"text":"others -- a genuine act of giving back."},{"time":87800,"text":"But there is something else\nthat was remarkable about it."},{"time":91000,"text":"It came completely out of the blue."},{"time":93080,"text":"There had been no market\nor stakeholder pressure,"},{"time":95720,"text":"and employees were so surprised"},{"time":97720,"text":"that they burst into tears\nwhen they heard the news."},{"time":101600,"text":"Actions like Ulukaya's are beautiful\nbecause they catch us off guard."},{"time":105480,"text":"They create something out of nothing"},{"time":108000,"text":"because they're completely unnecessary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112040,"text":"I once worked at a company"},{"time":114120,"text":"that was the result of a merger"},{"time":115720,"text":"of a large IT outsourcing firm\nand a small design firm."},{"time":119400,"text":"We were merging 9,000 software engineers"},{"time":121400,"text":"with 1,000 creative types."},{"time":123800,"text":"And to unify these\nimmensely different cultures,"},{"time":126560,"text":"we were going to launch\na third, new brand."},{"time":129639,"text":"And the new brand color\nwas going to be orange."},{"time":133160,"text":"And as we were going\nthrough the budget for the rollouts,"},{"time":136600,"text":"we decided last minute"},{"time":138680,"text":"to cut the purchase\nof 10,000 orange balloons,"},{"time":142360,"text":"which we had meant\nto distribute to all staff worldwide."},{"time":145800,"text":"They just seemed\nunnecessary and cute in the end."},{"time":149920,"text":"I didn't know back then"},{"time":151840,"text":"that our decision\nmarked the beginning of the end --"},{"time":154400,"text":"that these two organizations\nwould never become one."},{"time":157920,"text":"And sure enough,\nthe merger eventually failed."},{"time":160640,"text":"Now, was it because\nthere weren't any orange balloons?"},{"time":163480,"text":"No, of course not."},{"time":165880,"text":"But the kill-the-orange-balloons\nmentality permeated everything else."},{"time":171120,"text":"You might not always realize it,\nbut when you cut the unnecessary,"},{"time":174920,"text":"you cut everything."},{"time":177280,"text":"Leading with beauty means\nrising above what is merely necessary."},{"time":182760,"text":"So do not kill your orange balloons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187040,"text":"The second principle:"},{"time":188720,"text":"create intimacy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190080,"text":"[Create Intimacy]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":191480,"text":"Studies show that\nhow we feel about our workplace"},{"time":194320,"text":"very much depends on the relationships\nwith our coworkers."},{"time":197680,"text":"And what are relationships\nother than a string of microinteractions?"},{"time":201120,"text":"There are hundreds of these\nevery day in our organizations"},{"time":204360,"text":"that have the potential to distinguish\na good life from a beautiful one."},{"time":209480,"text":"The marriage researcher John Gottman says"},{"time":211480,"text":"that the secret of a healthy relationship"},{"time":214120,"text":"is not the great gesture\nor the lofty promise,"},{"time":217200,"text":"it's small moments of attachment."},{"time":220200,"text":"In other words, intimacy."},{"time":223120,"text":"In our networked organizations,"},{"time":224680,"text":"we tout the strength of weak ties"},{"time":227320,"text":"but we underestimate\nthe strength of strong ones."},{"time":230200,"text":"We forget the words of the writer\nRichard Bach who once said,"},{"time":233120,"text":"\"Intimacy --"},{"time":234360,"text":"not connectedness --"},{"time":235600,"text":"intimacy is the opposite of loneliness.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":238920,"text":"So how do we design\nfor organizational intimacy?"},{"time":243480,"text":"The humanitarian organization CARE"},{"time":245360,"text":"wanted to launch\na campaign on gender equality"},{"time":247760,"text":"in villages in northern India."},{"time":250120,"text":"But it realized quickly"},{"time":251400,"text":"that it had to have this conversation\nfirst with its own staff."},{"time":254960,"text":"So it invited all 36 team members\nand their partners"},{"time":260040,"text":"to one of the Khajuraho Temples,"},{"time":261800,"text":"known for their famous erotic sculptures."},{"time":265520,"text":"And there they openly discussed\ntheir personal relationships --"},{"time":269120,"text":"their own experiences of gender equality"},{"time":272520,"text":"with the coworkers and the partners."},{"time":275040,"text":"It was eye-opening for the participants."},{"time":277360,"text":"Not only did it allow them\nto relate to the communities they serve,"},{"time":281400,"text":"it also broke down invisible barriers"},{"time":283960,"text":"and created a lasting bond\namongst themselves."},{"time":286200,"text":"Not a single team member\nquit in the next four years."},{"time":291200,"text":"So this is how you create intimacy."},{"time":293720,"text":"No masks ..."},{"time":295920,"text":"or lots of masks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297560,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":298800,"text":"When Danone, the food company,"},{"time":300280,"text":"wanted to translate its new company\nmanifesto into product initiatives,"},{"time":304520,"text":"it gathered the management team"},{"time":306720,"text":"and 100 employees\nfrom across different departments,"},{"time":310360,"text":"seniority levels and regions"},{"time":312000,"text":"for a three-day strategy retreat."},{"time":314800,"text":"And it asked everybody\nto wear costumes for the entire meeting:"},{"time":318280,"text":"wigs, crazy hats, feather boas,"},{"time":321400,"text":"huge glasses and so on."},{"time":323560,"text":"And they left with concrete outcomes"},{"time":325840,"text":"and full of enthusiasm."},{"time":328040,"text":"And when I asked the woman\nwho had designed this experience"},{"time":331040,"text":"why it worked,"},{"time":332280,"text":"she simply said, \"Never underestimate\nthe power of a ridiculous wig.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":336120,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":337320,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":340880,"text":"Because wigs erase hierarchy,"},{"time":344080,"text":"and hierarchy kills intimacy --"},{"time":345960,"text":"both ways,"},{"time":347200,"text":"for the CEO and the intern."},{"time":349440,"text":"Wigs allow us to use\nthe disguise of the false"},{"time":353600,"text":"to show something true about ourselves."},{"time":357120,"text":"And that's not easy\nin our everyday work lives,"},{"time":359360,"text":"because the relationship\nwith our organizations"},{"time":361720,"text":"is often like that of a married couple\nthat has grown apart,"},{"time":366240,"text":"suffered betrayals and disappointments,"},{"time":369280,"text":"and is now desperate to be beautiful\nfor one another once again."},{"time":373880,"text":"And for either of us the first step\ntowards beauty involves a huge risk."},{"time":378520,"text":"The risk to be ugly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":379760,"text":"[Be Ugly]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":381120,"text":"So many organizations these days\nare keen on designing beautiful workplaces"},{"time":385400,"text":"that look like anything but work:"},{"time":387040,"text":"vacation resorts, coffee shops,\nplaygrounds or college campuses --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":391080,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":392320,"text":"Based on the promises\nof positive psychology,"},{"time":394520,"text":"we speak of play and gamification,"},{"time":397920,"text":"and one start-up even says\nthat when someone gets fired,"},{"time":401480,"text":"they have graduated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402800,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":404800,"text":"That kind of beautiful language\nonly goes \"skin deep,"},{"time":408320,"text":"but ugly cuts clean to the bone,\""},{"time":412240,"text":"as the writer Dorothy Parker once put it."},{"time":414480,"text":"To be authentic is to be ugly."},{"time":418800,"text":"It doesn't mean that you can't have fun\nor must give in to the vulgar or cynical,"},{"time":423240,"text":"but it does mean that you speak\nthe actual ugly truth."},{"time":427760,"text":"Like this manufacturer"},{"time":429040,"text":"that wanted to transform\none of its struggling business units."},{"time":432800,"text":"It identified, named and pinned\non large boards all the issues --"},{"time":436240,"text":"and there were hundreds of them --"},{"time":437920,"text":"that had become obstacles\nto better performance."},{"time":440240,"text":"They put them on boards,\nmoved them all into one room,"},{"time":442840,"text":"which they called \"the ugly room.\""},{"time":445120,"text":"The ugly became visible\nfor everyone to see --"},{"time":447520,"text":"it was celebrated."},{"time":449360,"text":"And the ugly room served as a mix\nof mirror exhibition and operating room --"},{"time":453240,"text":"a biopsy on the living flesh\nto cut out all the bureaucracy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":458640,"text":"The ugliest part of our body is our brain."},{"time":462640,"text":"Literally and neurologically."},{"time":465200,"text":"Our brain renders ugly\nwhat is unfamiliar ..."},{"time":469440,"text":"modern art, atonal music,"},{"time":471440,"text":"jazz, maybe --"},{"time":472680,"text":"VR goggles for that matter --"},{"time":474400,"text":"strange objects, sounds and people."},{"time":478320,"text":"But we've all been ugly once."},{"time":480520,"text":"We were a weird-looking baby,"},{"time":482880,"text":"a new kid on the block, a foreigner."},{"time":485960,"text":"And we will be ugly again\nwhen we don't belong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491320,"text":"The Center for Political Beauty,"},{"time":493240,"text":"an activist collective in Berlin,"},{"time":494880,"text":"recently staged an extreme\nartistic intervention."},{"time":498200,"text":"With the permission of relatives,"},{"time":500120,"text":"it exhumed the corpses of refugees\nwho had drowned at Europe's borders,"},{"time":504280,"text":"transported them all the way to Berlin,"},{"time":506200,"text":"and then reburied them\nat the heart of the German capital."},{"time":510400,"text":"The idea was to allow them\nto reach their desired destination,"},{"time":514120,"text":"if only after their death."},{"time":516960,"text":"Such acts of beautification\nmay not be pretty,"},{"time":520000,"text":"but they are much needed."},{"time":521280,"text":"Because things tend to get ugly\nwhen there's only one meaning, one truth,"},{"time":524760,"text":"only answers and no questions."},{"time":526880,"text":"Beautiful organizations\nkeep asking questions."},{"time":530480,"text":"They remain incomplete,"},{"time":533275,"text":"which is the fourth\nand the last of the principles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":535680,"text":"[Remain Incomplete]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":537240,"text":"Recently I was in Paris,"},{"time":539400,"text":"and a friend of mine\ntook me to Nuit Debout,"},{"time":542400,"text":"which stands for \"up all night,\""},{"time":543960,"text":"the self-organized protest movement"},{"time":545920,"text":"that had formed in response\nto the proposed labor laws in France."},{"time":550680,"text":"Every night, hundreds gathered\nat the Place de la RÃ©publique."},{"time":553920,"text":"Every night they set up\na small, temporary village"},{"time":556520,"text":"to deliberate their own vision\nof the French Republic."},{"time":560120,"text":"And at the core of this adhocracy"},{"time":562800,"text":"was a general assembly\nwhere anybody could speak"},{"time":565080,"text":"using a specially designed sign language."},{"time":568920,"text":"Like Occupy Wall Street\nand other protest movements,"},{"time":572200,"text":"Nuit Debout was born\nin the face of crisis."},{"time":575120,"text":"It was messy --"},{"time":576600,"text":"full of controversies and contradictions."},{"time":579920,"text":"But whether you agreed\nwith the movement's goals or not,"},{"time":582720,"text":"every gathering was\na beautiful lesson in raw humanity."},{"time":587640,"text":"And how fitting that Paris --"},{"time":589680,"text":"the city of ideals, the city of beauty --"},{"time":592480,"text":"was it's stage."},{"time":593720,"text":"It reminds us that like great cities,"},{"time":595560,"text":"the most beautiful organizations\nare ideas worth fighting for --"},{"time":599760,"text":"even and especially\nwhen their outcome is uncertain."},{"time":603480,"text":"They are movements;"},{"time":604800,"text":"they are always imperfect,\nnever fully organized,"},{"time":607160,"text":"so they avoid ever becoming banal."},{"time":609880,"text":"They have something\nbut we don't know what it is."},{"time":612240,"text":"They remain mysterious;\nwe can't take our eyes off them."},{"time":615200,"text":"We find them beautiful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619240,"text":"So to do the unnecessary,"},{"time":621120,"text":"to create intimacy,"},{"time":622800,"text":"to be ugly,"},{"time":624320,"text":"to remain incomplete --"},{"time":626560,"text":"these are not only the qualities\nof beautiful organizations,"},{"time":629560,"text":"these are inherently\nhuman characteristics."},{"time":632600,"text":"And these are also the qualities\nof what we call home."},{"time":637520,"text":"And as we disrupt, and are disrupted,"},{"time":639960,"text":"the least we can do is to ensure"},{"time":642280,"text":"that we still feel at home\nin our organizations,"},{"time":646320,"text":"and that we use our organizations\nto create that feeling for others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":650600,"text":"Beauty can save the world\nwhen we embrace these principles"},{"time":653720,"text":"and design for them."},{"time":656160,"text":"In the face of artificial intelligence\nand machine learning,"},{"time":659400,"text":"we need a new radical humanism."},{"time":661760,"text":"We must acquire and promote\na new aesthetic and sentimental education."},{"time":667320,"text":"Because if we don't,"},{"time":669360,"text":"we might end up feeling like aliens"},{"time":671840,"text":"in organizations and societies\nthat are full of smart machines"},{"time":675880,"text":"that have no appreciation whatsoever"},{"time":678720,"text":"for the unnecessary,"},{"time":680360,"text":"the intimate,"},{"time":681640,"text":"the incomplete"},{"time":683360,"text":"and definitely not for the ugly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685760,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":687000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}